## Compare Before vs After Scaling

```python
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

scaler     = StandardScaler()
df_scaled  = pd.DataFrame(
    scaler.fit_transform(df),
    columns=df.columns
)

# Plot before and after together
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))

df.boxplot(ax=ax1)
ax1.set_title("Before Scaling")

df_scaled.boxplot(ax=ax2)
ax2.set_title("After Scaling")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```

This is very useful in ML to see if features are on the **same scale** before feeding into a model like KNN or SVM which are distance-based algorithms.
